OL,3,CThe chancellor's choice between
OL,4,CNational Insurance and income tax cuts
OL,6,FThe choice to be made tomorrow in the
OL,7,Fbudget by Jeremy Hunt, is Treasury
OL,8,Feconomics versus Downing Street
OL,9,Felectoral politics.
OL,11,FThe first would reward work and would
OL,12,Freduce costs for business (indirectly).
OL,14,FThe second would do the same, but
OL,15,Fwould also hand additional cash to
OL,16,Fcore Tory supporters, namely
OL,17,Fpensioners and those with investment
OL,18,Fincome (from property rentals, share
OL,19,Fdividends, interest in savings and so
OL,20,Fon).
